  "soap_summary": "Patient reports a few-days history of a dry, itchy, red rash on the hands and arms that began after swimming. No prior eczema. No fever, vomiting, faintness, bleeding/discharge, urinary problems, or loose stools. Patient is currently taking Microgynon (combined oral contraceptive). Physician suspects dermatitis (unconfirmed) and recommends topical steroid cream, regular emollient use, and over-the-counter antihistamines (chlorphenamine or loratadine). Advise follow-up if not improved.",
